3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* maps 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* multi-dictionary search
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <maps.h>
10/*
11/* MAPS *maps_create(title, map_names, flags)
12/* const char *title;
13/* const char *map_names;
14/* int flags;
15/*
16/* const char *maps_find(maps, key, flags)
17/* MAPS *maps;
18/* const char *key;
19/* int flags;
20/*
21/* MAPS *maps_free(maps)
22/* MAPS *maps;
23/* DESCRIPTION
24/* This module implements multi-dictionary searches. it goes
25/* through the high-level dictionary interface and does file
26/* locking. Dictionaries are opened read-only, and in-memory
27/* dictionary instances are shared.
28/*
29/* maps_create() takes list of type:name pairs and opens the
30/* named dictionaries.
31/* The result is a handle that must be specified along with all
32/* other maps_xxx() operations.
33/* See dict_open(3) for a description of flags.
34/* This includes the flags that specify preferences for search
35/* string case folding.
36/*
37/* maps_find() searches the specified list of dictionaries
38/* in the specified order for the named key. The result is in
39/* memory that is overwritten upon each call.
40/* The flags argument is either 0 or specifies a filter:
41/* for example, DICT_FLAG_FIXED | DICT_FLAG_PATTERN selects
42/* dictionaries that have fixed keys or pattern keys.
43/*
44/* maps_free() releases storage claimed by maps_create()
45/* and conveniently returns a null pointer.
46/*
47/* Arguments:
48/* .IP title
49/* String used for diagnostics. Typically one specifies the
50/* type of information stored in the lookup tables.
51/* .IP map_names
52/* Null-terminated string with type:name dictionary specifications,
53/* separated by whitespace or commas.
54/* .IP flags
55/* With maps_create(), flags that are passed to dict_open().
56/* With maps_find(), flags that control searching behavior
57/* as documented above.
58/* .IP maps
59/* A result from maps_create().
60/* .IP key
61/* Null-terminated string with a lookup key. Table lookup is case
62/* sensitive.
63/* DIAGNOSTICS
64/* Panic: inappropriate use; fatal errors: out of memory, unable
65/* to open database. Warnings: null string lookup result.
66/*
67/* maps_find() returns a null pointer when the requested
68/* information was not found, and logs a warning when the
69/* lookup failed due to error. The maps->error value indicates
70/* if the last lookup failed due to error.
71/* BUGS
72/* The dictionary name space is flat, so dictionary names allocated
73/* by maps_create() may collide with dictionary names allocated by
74/* other methods.
75/*
76/* This functionality could be implemented by allowing the user to
77/* specify dictionary search paths to dict_lookup() or dict_eval().
78/* However, that would either require that the dict(3) module adopts
79/* someone else's list notation syntax, or that the dict(3) module
80/* imposes syntax restrictions onto other software, neither of which
81/* is desirable.
82/* LICENSE
83/* .ad
84/* .fi
85/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
86/* AUTHOR(S)
87/* Wietse Venema
88/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
89/* P.O. Box 704
90/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
91/*--*/
92

112/* maps_create - initialize */
113
114MAPS *maps_create(const char *title, const char *map_names, int dict_flags)
115{
116 const char *myname = "maps_create";
117 char *temp;
118 char *bufp;
119 static char sep[] = CHARS_COMMA_SP;
120 static char parens[] = CHARS_BRACE;
121 MAPS *maps;
122 char *map_type_name;
123 VSTRING *map_type_name_flags;
124 DICT *dict;
125
126 /*
127 * Initialize.
128 */
129 maps = (MAPS *) mymalloc(sizeof(*maps));
130 maps->title = mystrdup(title);
131 maps->argv = argv_alloc(2);
132 maps->error = 0;
133
134 /*
135 * For each specified type:name pair, either register a new dictionary,
136 * or increment the reference count of an existing one.
137 */
138 if (*map_names) {
139 bufp = temp = mystrdup(map_names);
140 map_type_name_flags = vstring_alloc(10);
141
142#define OPEN_FLAGS O_RDONLY
143
144 while ((map_type_name = mystrtokq(&bufp, sep, parens)) != 0) {
145 vstring_sprintf(map_type_name_flags, "%s(%o,%s)",
146 map_type_name, OPEN_FLAGS,
147 dict_flags_str(dict_flags));
148 if ((dict = dict_handle(vstring_str(map_type_name_flags))) == 0)
149 dict = dict_open(map_type_name, OPEN_FLAGS, dict_flags);
150 if ((dict->flags & dict_flags) != dict_flags)
151 msg_panic("%s: map %s has flags 0%o, want flags 0%o",
152 myname, map_type_name, dict->flags, dict_flags);
153 dict_register(vstring_str(map_type_name_flags), dict);
154 argv_add(maps->argv, vstring_str(map_type_name_flags), ARGV_END);
155 }
156 myfree(temp);
157 vstring_free(map_type_name_flags);
158 }
159 return (maps);
160}
161
162/* maps_find - search a list of dictionaries */
163
164const char *maps_find(MAPS *maps, const char *name, int flags)
165{
166 const char *myname = "maps_find";
167 char **map_name;
168 const char *expansion;
169 DICT *dict;
170
171 /*
172 * In case of return without map lookup (empty name or no maps).
173 */
174 maps->error = 0;
175
176 /*
177 * Temp. workaround, for buggy callers that pass zero-length keys when
178 * given partial addresses.
179 */
180 if (*name == 0)
181 return (0);
182
183 for (map_name = maps->argv->argv; *map_name; map_name++) {
184 if ((dict = dict_handle(*map_name)) == 0)
185 msg_panic("%s: dictionary not found: %s", myname, *map_name);
186 if (flags != 0 && (dict->flags & flags) == 0)
187 continue;
188 if ((expansion = dict_get(dict, name)) != 0) {
189 if (*expansion == 0) {
190 msg_warn("%s lookup of %s returns an empty string result",
191 maps->title, name);
192 msg_warn("%s should return NO RESULT in case of NOT FOUND",
193 maps->title);
194 maps->error = DICT_ERR_RETRY;
195 return (0);
196 }
197 if (msg_verbose)
198 msg_info("%s: %s: %s: %s = %s", myname, maps->title,
199 *map_name, name, expansion);
200 return (expansion);
201 } else if ((maps->error = dict->error) != 0) {
202 msg_warn("%s:%s lookup error for \"%.100s\"",
203 dict->type, dict->name, name);
204 break;
205 }
206 }
207 if (msg_verbose)
208 msg_info("%s: %s: %s: %s", myname, maps->title, name, maps->error ?
209 "search aborted" : "not found");
210 return (0);
211}
212
213/* maps_free - release storage */
214
215MAPS *maps_free(MAPS *maps)
216{
217 char **map_name;
218
219 for (map_name = maps->argv->argv; *map_name; map_name++) {
220 if (msg_verbose)
221 msg_info("maps_free: %s", *map_name);
222 dict_unregister(*map_name);
223 }
224 myfree(maps->title);
225 argv_free(maps->argv);
226 myfree((void *) maps);
227 return (0);
228}

230#ifdef TEST
231
232#include <vstring.h>
233#include <vstream.h>
234#include <vstring_vstream.h>
235
236int main(int argc, char **argv)
237{
238 VSTRING *buf = vstring_alloc(100);
239 MAPS *maps;
240 const char *result;
241
242 if (argc != 2)
243 msg_fatal("usage: %s maps", argv[0]);
244 msg_verbose = 2;
245 maps = maps_create("whatever", argv[1], DICT_FLAG_LOCK);
246
247 while (vstring_fgets_nonl(buf, VSTREAM_IN)) {
248 maps->error = 99;
249 vstream_printf("\"%s\": ", vstring_str(buf));
250 if ((result = maps_find(maps, vstring_str(buf), 0)) != 0) {
251 vstream_printf("%s\n", result);
252 } else if (maps->error != 0) {
253 vstream_printf("lookup error\n");
254 } else {
255 vstream_printf("not found\n");
256 }
257 vstream_fflush(VSTREAM_OUT);
258 }
259 maps_free(maps);
260 vstring_free(buf);
261 return (0);
262}
